Would like feedback on the new vulkano-shaders macro API.

This PR will need to wait for the stabilization of proc macros 2.0, which will happen in rust 1.30.
I'm pretty sure I'll need to remove the `#![feature(proc_macro_non_items)]` from the examples and just move the `vulkano_shader!` calls to the root of the module.

# Proposed syntax
Compact, consistent, everything is a field.
```rust
vulkano_shader!{
     mod_name: vertex_shader,
     ty: "vertex",
     src: "
#version 450

layout(location = 0) in vec3 position;

void main() {
   gl_Position = vec4(position, 1.0);
}"
}
```


# Alternative syntax

Tries to use the standard mod syntax to make it easier to understand what the mod setting does.
I included `Arguments` so its like a struct, otherwise its weird because a mod doesn't have fields.
I don't really like how this turned out at all, but I included it to hopefully motivate others to give some ideas.
```rust
vulkano_shader! {
    mod vs {
        Arguments {
            ty: "vertex",
            src: "
#version 450
layout(location = 0) in vec2 position;
void main() {
gl_Position = vec4(position, 0.0, 1.0);
}"
        }
    }
}
```
